## Version History

### v1.1.0 (2026-06-12)

Added the two empirically-confirmed R1/NOGO implementation gotchas discovered while
re-planning ProjectHephaestus issue #1214 (the prior plan was NOGO'd because the
proposed guard SCRIPT body would ship two mechanical defects):

- **Gotcha A — auto-discovering `--help` smoke-test contract.** `tests/unit/scripts/conftest.py`
  globs every `scripts/*.py` and parametrizes `test_scripts_smoke.py::test_script_help_exits_zero`,
  which runs `<script> --help` and asserts exit 0 AND non-empty stdout+stderr (unless the
  script is in `HELP_RUNS_REAL_WORK`). A guard whose `main()` ignores argv runs the silent
  real check on `--help` and fails on a clean repo, silently breaking a pre-existing test.
  Fix: mirror the template `--help`/`-h` branch verbatim (`print(__doc__); return 0`,
  `check_security_policy_no_hardcoded_date.py:44-45`) + add a direct `--help` unit test.
- **Gotcha B — `RUF100` rejects a `# noqa` for a non-enabled rule.** The ruff `select`
  does not include `S603`; a habitual `# noqa: S603` fires `RUF100 Unused noqa directive
  (non-enabled: S603)` → `ruff check` RED. Fix: grep the `select` list before any `# noqa`;
  a static-literal `subprocess.run` with no `shell=True` needs no noqa at all.
- **Meta-lesson (planning).** When a plan embeds full ready-to-commit file bodies, the
  reviewer lints/tests those bodies as the deliverable artifact; mentally run the repo's
  ACTUAL gates (auto-discovered/parametrized tests + exact ruff `select`) against the
  proposed code before submitting.

Edits: corrected the embedded script sketch to include the `--help` branch; added two
"When to Use" triggers (adding a new `scripts/*.py` to an auto-discovering harness; about
to add a `# noqa`) plus a planning trigger; added workflow steps 8/9/10 (Gotchas A/B + the
meta-lesson); added three R1/NOGO rows to the Failed Attempts table; added an R1 gotcha
table to Results & Parameters and an R1 row to "Verified On". Bumped the verification level
from `unverified` to `verified-local` (the audit facts and both gotchas were observed
directly; the full revised fix remains NOT CI-verified, called out explicitly in-body).

Verification level: verified-local for the FACTS — reviewer re-read
`tests/unit/scripts/test_scripts_smoke.py`, `tests/unit/scripts/conftest.py`, the template
`--help` branch at `check_security_policy_no_hardcoded_date.py:44-45`, and the
`pyproject.toml` ruff `select` list directly. The corrected script was NOT executed
end-to-end in CI.

### v1.0.0 (2026-06-12) — Snapshot

Original skill: guard a gitignored, name-colliding scratch dir (ProjectHephaestus `build/`)
against becoming git-TRACKED (not against on-disk runtime junk) via a `repo: local` Python
pre-commit hook asserting `git ls-files <dir>/` stays EMPTY. PLANNING learning from the
ProjectHephaestus #1214 strict audit; audit facts verified-local, proposed hook/script not
executed end-to-end. Full v1.0.0 content snapshot below.

